8. Ethical Considerations in Programming

Based on principles from the Association for Computing Machinery (ACM) Code of Ethics.

Privacy:
-No personal data collected
-No internet required
-Data stored locally
-Accessibility
-Clear prompts
-Simple menu layout
-Error handling included
-Intellectual Property

All code written by the team

Sources properly cited

